HEADWORD: Rivalry
<hw>Ri"val*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Rivalries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>The act of rivaling, or
the state of being a rival; a competition.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Keen contention
and eager <xex>rivalries</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Jeffrey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Emulation; competition. See
